:"56.9 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"28.3 g","calories":"3473 kJ \/ 830 kcal"},"preparations":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Preparation"},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Pastry"},{"content":"Place butter and flour in mixing bowl then chop <b>10 sec\/speed 8<b>."},{"content":"Add water then pulse <b>Turbo\/1 sec\/2-4 times<b> until just clinging together. Tip out, form into a ball then wrap in cling film and chill for 30 minutes."},{"content":"Roll out pastry on a lightly floured surface and use to line 6 tartlet tins (Ø 8-9 cm). Prick bases with a fork, then return to fridge for 15 minutes. Meanwhile, preheat oven to 180°C. Line pastry shells with baking paper and fill with baking beans then blind bake for 10-15 minutes (180°C) until baking paper can be removed easily. Remove beans and paper then bake for a further 10 minutes (180°C) until golden."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Mushroom Duxelle"},{"content":"Place shallot and butter in mixing bowl then chop <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add mushrooms then sauté <b>7 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add parsley, thyme, salt and pepper then blend <b>5 sec\/speed 9<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then blend again <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Transfer to a bowl and drizzle with truffle oil. Clean mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Stilton Rarebit"},{"content":"Place beer, Stilton and Cheddar in mixing bowl then heat <b>3 min\/90°C\/speed 4<b>."},{"content":"Add breadcrumbs, flour, egg, egg yolk, mustard and Worcestershire sauce then cook <b>5 min\/90°C\/speed 4<b>. Transfer to a bowl to cool. Clean mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Celeriac Purée"},{"content":"Place celeriac, cream, salt and pepper in mixing bowl then cook <b>20 min\/90°C\/speed 4<b>. Meanwhile, divide reserved mushroom duxelle between pastry cases then spread a heaped tablespoon of reserved rarebit on top of each. Keep purée warm after cooking."},{"content":"Bake tartlets for 10-15 minutes (180°C) until golden brown. Meanwhile, place steaks on a baking tray. Brush all over with a little olive oil then season with 1 pinch salt and 1 pinch black pepper per side. Roast (see tip) for 4-6 minutes (220°C), turning once, until cooked to taste, then cover with foil and rest for a minimum of 5 minutes. To serve, carve each fillet and serve on a plate with a tartlet and some celeriac purée scattered with chopped parsley."}],"hintsAndTricks":["If you have a double oven, preheat one to 180°C and one to 220°C, otherwise you can cook the steaks at the top, and tartlets in the lower part of the same oven.","Steaks may be pan-fried if preferred.","For a smooth celeriac purée, blend <strong>1 min\/speed 9<\/strong> after step 9."],"basicInfo":["medium","40m","2h 10m","6 portions"]}